  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2747",
  "title": "Multiple sortBySelector interfere with each other",
  "body": "I want to sort my orders by multiple attributes. I've created replicas for my primary index:\r\n![](https://cl.ly/2u451Z22460V/Image%202018-02-22%20at%202.14.59%20PM.png)\r\n\r\nThen, on my js (coffeescript), I use instantsearch for adding multiple sortBySelectors:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  search.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.sortBySelector\r\n      container: '#sortBySelectorUserName'\r\n      indices: [\r\n        { name: 'Order_development', label: 'User name' },\r\n        { name: 'order_user_name_asc', label: 'User name asc' },\r\n        { name: 'order_user_name_desc', label: 'User name desc' }\r\n      ],\r\n      cssClasses:\r\n        select: ['sort-by']\r\n  )\r\n\r\n  search.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.sortBySelector\r\n      container: '#sortBySelectorCustomerName'\r\n      indices: [\r\n        { name: 'Order_development', label: 'Customer name' },\r\n        { name: 'order_customer_name_asc', label: 'Customer name asc' },\r\n        { name: 'order_customer_name_desc', label: 'Customer name desc' }\r\n      ],\r\n      cssClasses:\r\n        select: ['sort-by']\r\n  )\r\n```\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, when I change one of the dropdowns, the other one gets affected as well:\r\n![](https://cl.ly/0F2R3z3a1c1H/Screen%20Recording%202018-02-22%20at%2002.18%20PM.gif)\r\n\r\nHow can I keep the label name on the other dropdowns while sorting?\r\nPerhaps I'm missing a key concept? ",
